<p>The margin on project work depends entirely on scoping accuracy. Underestimate the hours, and the project loses money. Overestimate, and the client chooses a cheaper competitor.</p>
<p>About 60% of agencies use project-based billing as a secondary revenue stream. Less than 10% operate on project-only models. The revenue unpredictability makes sustainable growth nearly impossible. Every month starts at zero. The team is either over capacity or underused depending on what closed last quarter.</p>
