<h3>The Specialization Premium</h3>
<p>The economics of specialization are significant and underappreciated. A dental marketing agency charging $4,000 per month per client needs 21 clients for $1 million in annual revenue. A generalist agency with the same revenue goal might need 30 or more clients, because their average contract value is lower.</p>
<p>More clients means more project management, more account calls, more churn surface area. Niche specialists working with a defined ideal customer profile on retainer can build to $1 million to $2 million per year. They do this with a team of 5 to 8 people and margins above 30%.</p>
<p>Generalist agencies often need 15 to 20 employees to hit the same revenue, with half the margin. Specialization is not a marketing strategy. It is a margin strategy.</p>
